      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Opening the Negotiation (T-45)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The first contact sets the frame. Lead with data, not with emotion. A well-structured opening email with the utilization report attached signals that this is a fact-based negotiation, not a bluff."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Example email to vendor AE (T-45 days)\nOPENING_EMAIL_TEMPLATE = \"\"\"\nSubject: {product_name} Renewal \u2014 {renewal_date} \u2014 Data Package Attached\n\nHi {ae_name},\n\nOur {product_name} contract renews on {renewal_date}. We've completed our annual\nutilization review and wanted to share the findings before discussing renewal terms.\n\nKey findings:\n- Current seats: {current_seats}\n- Peak active users (90-day trailing): {target_seats}\n- Seat utilization: {utilization_pct:.0f}%\n\nBased on this data, we're proposing to renew at {target_seats} seats.\nOur target budget for this renewal is ${opening_ask_usd:,.0f} annually.\n\nI've attached:\n1. Utilization report (90-day)\n2. Seat activity log\n\nHappy to discuss on a call this week. Are you available Thursday or Friday?\n\nBest,\n{sender_name}\nFinOps Team\n\"\"\"\n\ndef render_opening_email(playbook: RenewalPlaybook, ae_name: str, sender_name: str) -> str:\n    utilization = playbook.target_seats / playbook.current_seats * 100\n    return OPENING_EMAIL_TEMPLATE.format(\n        product_name=playbook.product_name,\n        renewal_date=playbook.renewal_date,\n        ae_name=ae_name,\n        current_seats=playbook.current_seats,\n        target_seats=playbook.target_seats,\n        utilization_pct=utilization,\n        opening_ask_usd=playbook.opening_ask_usd,\n        sender_name=sender_name,\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Escalation Ladder"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vendors sometimes stall, hoping the renewal date will force you into unfavourable terms. A predefined escalation ladder with triggers and deadlines keeps the process moving and ensures the right people are involved before time runs out."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom datetime import date, timedelta\n\n@dataclass\nclass EscalationStep:\n    trigger: str\n    action: str\n    contact: str\n    deadline: date\n\ndef build_escalation_ladder(\n    playbook: RenewalPlaybook,\n) -> list[EscalationStep]:\n    r = playbook.renewal_date\n    return [\n        EscalationStep(\n            trigger=\"No response from AE within 5 business days of opening email\",\n            action=\"CC AE's manager; resend with updated subject line\",\n            contact=playbook.vendor_contacts[1].email if len(playbook.vendor_contacts) > 1 else \"vendor support\",\n            deadline=r - timedelta(days=40),\n        ),\n        EscalationStep(\n            trigger=\"AE refuses seat reduction without VP approval\",\n            action=\"Request VP of Sales meeting; bring Finance sponsor\",\n            contact=\"VP Sales (via AE introduction)\",\n            deadline=r - timedelta(days=30),\n        ),\n        EscalationStep(\n            trigger=\"Vendor price exceeds walk-away after two rounds\",\n            action=\"Formally invoke BATNA: send notice of intent to switch\",\n            contact=playbook.batna.alternative,\n            deadline=r - timedelta(days=21),\n        ),\n        EscalationStep(\n            trigger=\"No agreement by T-14\",\n            action=\"Request 30-day extension to current contract while alternatives evaluated\",\n            contact=\"Vendor legal / contracts team\",\n            deadline=r - timedelta(days=14),\n        ),\n    ]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Invoking the BATNA (sending formal notice of intent to switch) is the strongest move available and should be reserved for T-21 or later. Do not invoke it unless you are genuinely prepared to switch \u2014 vendors who receive a bluff notice and call it lose trust in future negotiations."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "BATNA Development"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Request RFPs from 2\u20133 competitors at T-60"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": A live proposal is worth 10\u00d7 more than a published pricing page in a negotiation. Vendors know their competitors' list prices."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Calculate total switching cost honestly"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Migration work, integration changes, retraining, and productivity dip during transition. An underestimated switching cost weakens your position if the vendor calls the bluff."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Assess capability parity"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": A competitor at 40% lower cost is irrelevant if it lacks a feature critical to your workflow. Document parity gaps before presenting the quote."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Internal buy-in for switching"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Confirm that the engineering team and product owners would accept the switch before using it as a negotiating lever."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tracking Outcomes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Recording outcomes creates institutional memory across renewals, enables benchmarking of negotiation effectiveness, and provides data for the FinOps programme's annual savings report."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom datetime import date\n\n@dataclass\nclass NegotiationOutcome:\n    tool_id: str\n    renewal_date: date\n    scenario: NegotiationScenario\n    opening_ask_usd: float\n    walk_away_usd: float\n    final_agreed_usd: float\n    seats_agreed: int\n    term_years: int\n    concessions_given: list[str]\n    notes: str = \"\"\n\n    @property\n    def savings_vs_status_quo_usd(self) -> float:\n        # Status quo = renewing at same seats, same price\n        return (self.walk_away_usd - self.final_agreed_usd) * self.term_years\n\n    @property\n    def achieved_target(self) -> bool:\n        return self.final_agreed_usd <= self.walk_away_usd\n\n    @property\n    def negotiation_effectiveness(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"How far between opening ask and walk-away did we land?\"\"\"\"\n        if self.final_agreed_usd <= self.opening_ask_usd:\n            return \"EXCEEDED\"\n        ratio = (self.final_agreed_usd - self.opening_ask_usd) / (self.walk_away_usd - self.opening_ask_usd)\n        return \"STRONG\" if ratio < 0.33 else \"ACCEPTABLE\" if ratio < 0.66 else \"WEAK\""
          }
        ]
      },
